-- Barclays Hires Macdonald as Head of Europe, Asia Loans as Ritchie Retires
-- Patricia Kuo
-- 2010-07-21T16:03:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-21/barclays-hires-macdonald-as-head-of-europe-asia-loans-as-ritchie-retires.html

          
          
             Barclays Capital , the investment
banking arm of Barclays Plc, hired former UBS AG banker  Jonathan Macdonald  as head of global loan syndications for Europe and the
Asia-Pacific region.  
 Tim Ritchie , head of global loan syndicate, will retire in
September after more than 30 years with the London-based bank.  
 Macdonald will be based in London and report to Mark
Bamford, global head of fixed-income syndicate, according to a
Barclays Capital internal memo. A company spokesman confirmed
the content of the memo.  
 Macdonald was head of global syndicated finance for Europe
and Asia at UBS until 2009.  
 Barclays Capital is the fourth-largest syndicated loan
arranger in Europe this year, with a 5 percent market share,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  
